Description: CoMorTrax is a comprehensive framework for comorbidity analysis
    integrating differential expression, interaction effect quantification,
    network rewiring analysis, cell-type vulnerability scoring, and machine
    learning classification for single-cell multi-omics data. Unlike
    conventional tools that analyze diseases independently, CoMorTrax explicitly
    models non-additive molecular interactions that emerge when two or more
    diseases co-exist in the same cell. Core modules include: multi-label
    disease encoding, comorbidity-aware differential expression (Wilcoxon,
    edgeR, MAST), permutation-based synergy and antagonism scoring,
    pathway-level comorbidity enrichment, composite cell-type vulnerability
    scoring, gene regulatory network rewiring analysis, machine-learning
    comorbidity state prediction (Random Forest, LASSO, Elastic Net), and
    optional spatial transcriptomics mapping. Validated on five published
    single-cell datasets spanning Alzheimer Disease, Type 2 Diabetes,
    Parkinson Disease, Lupus, and Heart Failure comorbidities.
